page.text: Intersection: NC Highway 11 / NC Highway 903 (North Main Street) at
Mekuria Engineering, Inc. ● Post Office Box 10505, Raleigh, NC 27605 ● www.mekuriaengineering.com ● phone: 919.833.8743
Data Collection Method: Jamar Count Board
1) Kenansville Elementary School is located less than 1 mile from
the studied intersection, however was not in session on the
date of the count, as Duplin County Schools were out of session
for summer break on the date of the count.
2) Pedestrians were observed and counted. One disabled
pedestrian, utilizing a motorized wheelchair, was observed
crossing the westbound leg of the intersection.
3) NB & SB approach grades are 1%, and EB & WB are 0%.
4) Area lighting was present at the count location.
5) No highway construction was observed that impacted normal traffic patterns.
6) Data collection equipment was operating correctly at time of count.
7) Counter took breaks from 9:15 – 9:30 AM and 2:15 – 2:30 PM. Data for these periods was interpolated.
8) Counter Notes: The eastbound leg of the intersection is designated in the field as a one way entrance only;
however the counter observed and counted several vehicles exiting at this location.
